    </note>
    <para id="para-00019">Looking at the truth table for the conditional statement, the only time the conditional is true is when the hypothesis <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><mi>p</mi></math> is also true. The only place this happens is in the first row, where <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><mi>q</mi></math> is also true, confirming that the law of detachment is a valid argument.</para>
