    <para id="para-00037" xmlns="http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml">To verify the chain rule for conditional arguments, construct a truth table for the argument, <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>∧</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>q</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>→</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></math>, and verify that it is a tautology.</para>
